	h2 Streets
	.story Strolling around the Kuta town, you get a sense of how commercialised it is. The beach front is lined up with hotels after resorts after hotels. We found ourselves in Beach Walk Shopping Centres that looked a cookie-cutter mall from Singapore. All the shops with the major brands were there. If you sneak behind the front line, that's where you find small streets with shops, backpacker's inns, restaurants, houses, and temples. The shops sold crafts, ornaments, and clothes. The Hindu temples had depictions of Gods carved into the structure. The locals were religious. Every morning, you will find fresh colorful offerings laid on the floor outside the shops. 
