	h2 Parasailing
	.story Parasailing was the highlight of the trip. It was what we came for - to be hooked up to a parachute and tethered to a speedboat moving at top speed. The forward motion generates a lift on the parachute like a kite. High up in the air, people, boats, and buildings looked like ants. We got a spectacular birds-eye view of Nusa Dua and beyond. That was close as I will ever get to flying. The sky was clear, the sun made the water sparkled on this balmy day. I was in heaven. After ten minutes, we floated back down to earth. It was over too quickly.
